title: Week 3 NFL Recap, Analysis; Daniel Jones the hero in 1st career start (Football 9/23)
description:
Will Brinson is joined by Ryan Wilson, John Breech and Sean Wagner-McGough to recap all the Week 3 Sunday action from around the NFL The guys react to Daniel Jones leading a rally in his first career start (1:00), Freddie Kitchens' blunders in the Browns loss to the Rams (13:30), and the hype of Mahomes vs Lamar in Chiefs-Ravens (25:30). The guys then focus on 3 young backup QBs filling in for injured vets as Mason Rudolph wasn't put in the best spot to succeed by the Steelers (40:00), Teddy Bridgewater did enough to beat the Seahawks (44:00), while Kyle Allen impressed vs the Cardinals (51:00). Will, Ryan, John and Sean also recap Lions-Eagles (56:00), Dolphins-Cowboys (1:01:00) and Jets-Patriots (1:05:00). The guys finish up by discussing Bengals-Bills (1:0900), Broncos-Packers (1:12:00), Falcons-Colts (1:18:00), Raiders-Vikings (1:23:00) and lastly Chargers-Texans (1:37:00).
